1. Introduction
1.1 Overview
This project implements a machine learning system that predicts house prices using Linear Regression. The system analyzes property features (size, rooms, location) to provide automated price estimates.
1.2 Motivation
Real estate pricing is complex and time-consuming. Manual valuations are:
•	Inconsistent across different evaluators
•	Slow and resource-intensive
•	Subject to human bias
An automated ML-based solution provides fast, consistent, data-driven predictions.
1.3 Technologies Used
•	Language: Python 3.7+
•	Libraries: Pandas, Scikit-learn, NumPy, Matplotlib
•	Algorithm: Linear Regression with One-Hot Encoding
