6. Design Decisions & Rationale
6.1 Linear Regression
Why: Simple, fast, interpretable. Provides good baseline.
Trade-off: May miss non-linear patterns.
6.2 One-Hot Encoding
Why: Locations have no ordinal relationship.
Alternative: Label encoding would imply false ordering.
6.3 80/20 Train-Test Split
Why: Standard practice, balances training data with evaluation.
Limitation: With 10 samples, only 2 for testing.
6.4 RMSE Metric
Why: Same units as price (dollars), penalizes large errors.
Supplement: Could add R², MAE for complete picture.
