7. Implementation
 Key Implementation Steps
1.	Data Creation: 10 houses with size (850-3000 sqft), rooms (2-6), locations (A/B/C)
2.	Feature Encoding: One-Hot encodes location → 3 binary columns
3.	Split: 8 houses for training, 2 for testing
4.	Training: Model learns: Price = β₀ + β₁(Size) + β₂(Rooms) + β₃(Loc_A) + β₄(Loc_B) + β₅(Loc_C)
5.	Evaluation: RMSE measures average prediction error
6.	Visualization: Scatter plot shows prediction accuracy
